HEADWORD: irredentism
<hw>irredentism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the doctrine that irredenta
should be controlled by the country to which they are ethnically or
historically related.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> irridentism.</syn>⟦br⟧
